Here is a workaround:
- Declare the spring-boot plugin in the dependency management section of your parent pom
- Explicitly skip the plugin execution in your common submodules:
```
            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;configuration&gt;
                    &lt;skip&gt;true&lt;/skip&gt;
                &lt;/configuration&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
```
- Execute the plugin for your submodule: `mvn --projects A,B,D --also-make clean install spring-boot:build-image`

